.TH GETPID 2 "2025" "Nightingale" "Nightingale System Calls"
.SH NAME
getpid, gettid \- get process and thread identification
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <unistd.h>
.PP
.B pid_t getpid(void);
.B pid_t gettid(void);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B getpid()
returns the process ID (PID) of the calling process.
.PP
.B gettid()
returns the thread ID (TID) of the calling thread.
.PP
In Nightingale, processes are identified by the format
.BR [pid:tid] .
The PID identifies the process (group of threads sharing an address space),
while the TID identifies the specific thread within that process.
.SH RETURN VALUE
These calls are always successful and return the appropriate identifier.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR fork (2),
.BR clone0 (2),
.BR setpgid (2)
